TunableList.display: Customer Rating Delta To Business Star Rating Value Change Curve
TunableList.description:
When a customer is done with their meal, we will take the delta between their rating and the business rating and map that to an amount it should change the star rating value for the restaurant.
For instance, the business has a current rating of 3 stars and the customer is giving a rating of 4.5 stars. 4.5 - 3 = a delta of 1.5. That 1.5 will map, on this curve, to the amount we should adjust the star rating value for the business.

TunableList.name: customer_star_rating_buff_bucket_data
TunableList.display: Customer Star Rating Buff Bucket Data
TunableList.description:
A mapping from Business Customer Star Rating Buff Bucket to the data associated with the buff bucker for this business.
Each buff bucket has a minimum, median, and maximum value. For every buff a customer has that falls within a buff bucket, that buff's Buff Bucket Delta is added to that bucket's totals. The totals are clamped between -1 and 1 and interpolated against the minimum/medium/maximum value for their associated buckets. All of the final values of the buckets are added together and that value is used in the Customer Star Buff Bucket To Rating Curve to determine the customer's final star rating of this business.
For instance, assume a buff bucket has a minimum value of -200, median of 0, and maximum of 100, and the buff bucket's clamped total is 0.5, the actual value of that bucket will be 50 (half way, or 0.5, between 0 and 100). If, however, the bucket's total is -0.5, we'd interpolate between the bucket's minimum value, -200, and median value, 0, to arrive at a bucket value of -100.
